# Summary

<div class="block">

![Example Band](/img/diagrams/calculus/surface-band.png)

The surface of revolution is the surface obtained by rotating a function around some axis (not necessarily the
standard ones). Often times, we are interested in determining the surface area of this surface, though generally
speaking we are interested in the system of parametric equations involved with creating said surface. 

The area of a surface of revolution can be derived by the surface area of a *band*, as generated by a smaller cone 
removed from a larger one. The lateral height of this band can be taken to be the [arc length](arc_length) of a given 
curve, made arbitrarily precise by increasing the number of polygonal approximations along said curve.

</div>

